    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-19T14:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-19T14:36:00-05:00" n="1071"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1071">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/252.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-19T13:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have no satisfactory answer to Department’s April 15, 8 p.m. I have had two
                    interviews with the Minister for Foreign Affairs, but have been unable to get
                    any definite reply. I advise the Department to act according to our own
                    obligations and the pressing necessities of the case, sending a small gunboat or
                    a transport if possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
